# General instructions

Language-agnostic rules for this project. Always load these. When working
in a specific language, also load the matching set under
`instructions/<language>/`.

| File | When to load |
| --- | --- |
| `coding-conventions.md` | Always. The baseline rules for naming, errors, comments, coupling. |
| `architecture.md` | Always. The DDD layering rules and the composition root. |
| `ddd.md` | Always. The modelling vocabulary — entities, value objects, aggregates, repositories, unit of work, ubiquitous language. |
| `tdd.md` | Whenever you're about to write or change behaviour. The red-green-refactor workflow and what makes a test valuable. |
| `testing.md` | Whenever you're authoring or running tests. Where each kind of test lives and what to test. |
| `security.md` | Whenever input crosses a boundary, secrets are handled, or auth is involved. |

## Reading order for a new contributor (human or agent)

1. `architecture.md` — the layout you're slotting into.
2. `ddd.md` — the modelling vocabulary the rest of the docs use.
3. `coding-conventions.md` — the baseline rules.
4. `tdd.md` and `testing.md` — how we work.
5. `security.md` — the boundary rules.

After that, jump to the language-specific subfolder for the language you're
about to touch.
